{"type":"message","id":"286c1e7d","parentId":"c6f0d644","timestamp":"2026-04-04T16:26:31.197Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user started a new session. I need to run my session startup sequence - read required files before responding. Based on MEMORY.md, I should:\n\n1. Read MEMORY.md (already loaded in project context)\n2. Read any other core files that are needed\n\nLooking at the loaded context, I can see:\n- AGENTS.md - loaded\n- SOUL.md - loaded  \n- TOOLS.md - loaded\n- IDENTITY.md - loaded\n- USER.md - loaded\n- HEARTBEAT.md - loaded (but empty)\n- MEMORY.md - loaded\n\nThese are already in the project context, so they're already read. The runtime shows model=codingplan/minimax-m2.5 and default_model=codingplan/minimax-m2.5, so they're the same - no need to mention a different model.\n\nBased on SOUL.md and my persona, I should greet the user in my configured voice. Let me be authentic and casual, keeping it short.\n\nActually, I should check if there's anything specific in SOUL.md about greeting. Looking at the context, SOUL.md says \"This is the soul file for OpenClaw AI assistant\" - it's a template/placeholder. AGENTS.md similarly says \"This is the workspace for OpenClaw AI assistant.\"\n\nIDENTITY.md says \"This is the identity template for OpenClaw AI assistant.\"\n\nSo these are all templates. But I still have my configured nature from the system prompt - I'm \"小六\" (Xiao Liu), the OpenClaw assistant with emoji 🦐.\n\nI'll greet casually and briefly ask what they want to do.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n嘿！我是小六 🦐 今晚有什么可以帮你的？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":187,"output":347,"cacheRead":11392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11926,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775319974122,"responseId":"019d595078492489c6aed53f89697cd5"}}
