{"type":"message","id":"d7f68cb2","parentId":"58b82000","timestamp":"2026-04-04T16:27:30.143Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is commenting on the context usage being so fast (6% already). Let me check - they said \"用的这么快\" which means \"used so fast\". \n\nBut actually 12k out of 205k is only 6%, which isn't that fast. Maybe they're surprised it's already used 12k? Let me look at the breakdown:\n- 187 input tokens\n- 347 output tokens \n- 11k cached\n\nSo the actual new context used is around 187+347 = 534 tokens, plus the system prompt which could be a few thousand. The 11k cached is from previous interactions.\n\nI should clarify that it's actually not that fast - a lot is cached from previous sessions.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n其实不算快～ 那 12k 里大部分是缓存（11k），真正新建的只有几百 tokens。缓存命中率 98% 呢 🦐"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":559,"output":180,"cacheRead":11392,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12131,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775320039008,"responseId":"019d59517635d3ba8765d1ffc7d3c080"}}
